CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 22, 1959, pg. A10 reads: "Anniversary Guests - Among the scores of guests who filled the home of Dr. and Mrs. James Henry of Cherokee St., last Saturday night on the anniversary of their silver year, were these out-of-towners. Left, Mr. and Mrs. Douglass Henry, Cincinnati; Mrs. Ella Christian, west Palm Beach, Fla. Atty and Mrs. Carl Stokes, Cleveland; Mrs. Florence Davis, Petersburg, Va., and Mr. and Mrs. Clarence Rogers, Cleveland. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of out-of-town guests, from left: Mr. and Mrs. Douglass Henry, Ella Christian, Atty. and Mrs. Carl Stokes, Florence Davis, and Mr. and Mrs. Clarence Roger, posed in home of Dr. and Mrs. James Henry's home on Cherokee Street for 25th wedding anniversary
